summary: The upcoming Republican National Convention focuses on the absent former president. Vice President Pence criticized the RNC platform as "deeply disappointing," particularly regarding abortion rights. President Trump replaced Pence with J.D. Vance as his running mate, who many believe would have acted differently than Pence on January 6th. Pence and other Republicans opposed to abortion have denounced the RNC platform changes. The Biden campaign has highlighted Vance's potential role in a similar situation to January 6th. Several former RNC Convention speakers, including Pence, have withdrawn their support for Trump. Pence has expressed his disappointment with the platform changes, and the showrunner of the TV show "Veep" draws parallels between Mike Pence and the show's protagonist, Selina Meyer. Trump's selection of J.D. Vance as his running mate reinforces his commitment to his platform.

Higgins' contract situation makes him a potential free agent in 2025, leading to rumors of a possible trade. Meanwhile, Higgins has been spotted with a former teammate, hinting at potential destinations. Despite being the only franchised player in 2024 without an extension, Higgins is reportedly content with his current status and remains committed to the Bengals.

Despite his young age, Alcaraz has consistently excelled on the court, making it to the Wimbledon semifinals and showcasing his exceptional athleticism. His success extends beyond Wimbledon, as he has also captured a major title at the Euro 2024 tournament.
